doc.previous: Nesbitt found a number of further potential synapomorphies and discounted a number of synapomorphies previously suggested Some of these are also present in silesaurids which Nesbitt recovered as a sister group to Dinosauria including a large anterior trochanter metatarsals II and IV of subequal length reduced contact between ischium and pubis the presence of a cnemial crest on the tibia and of an ascending process on the astragalus and many others 12
